<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1975-10-08T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1975-10-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="136" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d136">
                        <head>136. Minutes of the Secretary of State’s Staff Meeting, Washington,
                            October 8, 1975.<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d136fn1">Source:
                                National Archives, <gloss target="#t_rg">RG</gloss> 59, Transcripts
                                of Secretary of State <persName corresp="#p_kissinger-henry-a">Kissinger</persName>’s Staff Meetings, 1973–1977, E5177, Box 8.
                                Secret. At the 8 a.m. meeting on October 31, <persName corresp="#p_miller-robert-h">Robert H. Miller</persName>, Acting
                                Assistant Secretary of State for East Asian and Pacific Affairs,
                                said, “The Indonesian Foreign Minister is expected to open talks
                                tomorrow on Timor. The pro-Indonesian forces are gradually making
                                progress on the ground.” <persName corresp="#p_kissinger-henry-a">Kissinger</persName> remarked, “It is going to wind up with
                                Timor going to Indonesia.” <persName corresp="#p_miller-robert-h">Miller</persName> replied, “I think so. Maybe within a couple
                                of months.” (Ibid., Box 9)</note>
                            <note n="2" type="summary" xml:id="d136fn2">
                                <persName corresp="#p_habib-philip-c">Habib</persName> and <persName corresp="#p_kissinger-henry-a">Kissinger</persName> discussed
                                the situation in Portuguese Timor.</note>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline>
                                <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-head" calendar="gregorian" when="1975-10-08">October 8, 1975</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
